node.text:
I love running for the simplicity, the suffering, the rollercoaster, the possibilities, and the memories created with friends. And the post-run snacks. 😊 
•••
Had a great time with @kodiakcakes getting some footage for this short video. Thanks, team! Soaking up these views with you all was so fun. 🏜
•••
#deweytoit #kodiakcakes

May be an image of 1 person, standing and nature.

node.text:
DNF Hardrock. 😔 I’m bummed but also reminded how cool & unpredictable this sport is. Hope to get the chance to try this one again sometime - those mountains were so fun to play in and my legs were so ready to play! 🏔 Stomach issues early turned into bigger issues later, so it looks like we have some reflecting and adjusting to do. Always learning and trying to be better. On to the next!
•••
Congrats to @francois_dhaene on the win and killer Course Record! Allez! And @sabrinaleannstanley for back-to-back wins on this amazing, tough course! 💪🎉
•••
📷 @trailjunkiephotos
•••

node.text:
And we’re off! 100 miles of wild & tough mountain terrain here we come! ⛏👷‍♀️ Thanks for the good vibes, and biggest bear hugs to my crew for joining me in this adventure. 🐻💚 Have a great weekend! ✌️
•••
Ways you can follow along:
🔸Race tracking link in bio. Bib #118
🔸Follow @irunfar on Twitter for live updates along the course.
•••
📷 @howiesternphoto
•••

node.text:
Time to get the chisel out, it’s race week! ⛏👷‍♀️ Very excited to experience the @hardrock100run, spend some time in my Pain Cave, and be back with the ultra community. Race starts Friday. There will be tracking so stay tuned on how you can follow along! Let’s goooo! 🏔🎉
•••

node.text:
So much crew love. Even in a run where just one person’s feet travel the entire distance, it feels like a team sport. These are all from the Colorado Trail attempt last summer. While we didn’t make it all the way to Denver, that week of sharing the trails with this group is still one of my favorite running memories. Thanks to all the crews out there for helping us keep moving! Your jokes, cooking, hugs, and brainpower when ours turn to mush are so, so appreciated! 💚🍻 Hopefully my crew won’t mind joining me out there again someday! 😉
•••
📷 @_cammcleod_ 
•••

node.text:
Always wanted to “Everest” something! Climbing the height of the world’s tallest mountain (29,032ft 🏔) in one day is a silly idea that is best shared with a friend. Thanks, @meghanmhicks, that was ridiculous & so fun. We made laps of a 900ft climb in Moab, ate boatloads of snacks, and watched the light change on the rocks around us for about 21 hours/60ish miles. What a day! Also, check out the unexpected and delicious dinner brought to us!😍🍔🙏
•••
📷 @ez_gone_coddiwompling
•••

node.text:
12 miles from the finish of a 100 mile race, my vision faded to pure white. I couldn’t see my hand in front of my face*.😳 Part of what I love about longer ultras is that there is usually an unexpected wrench thrown in the day. I love surprises! 🔧🥳 When the wrench shows up, I try to stay very fact-based and not let emotions take over. What is the problem? Have I had something like this happen before? Am I okay and is this safe? What are the things that ARE working? For this particular problem, if I looked straight down, I could make out a small arc of trail in front of my toes. This was the solution for getting to the finish line. Stay calm and clear-headed so you can find the way forward!
•••
*Best guess for what happened to my eyes was corneal edema. My vision came back within 5-6 hours of finishing. Now I use eye drops and wear protective eyewear during races to help prevent it from happening again. 👓
•••
📷 @trailjunkiephotos at the 2017 @rrr_steamboat
•••
